{
  "rationale": "To ensure efficient and systematic coverage while reacting safely to obstacles, we introduce helper states to manage obstacle avoidance and systematic turning. Each state reacts to uncontrollable events by switching to the appropriate obstacle-aware mode, and controllable events are used to encourage wall-following and pattern-based coverage. This structure prevents oscillations by requiring a full rotation only after repeated obstacle encounters, and encourages forward movement when possible.",
